Code Page 949 Encoding and Decoding

Published August 12, 2024
By Samuel Yang

Code Page 949 (CP949) is a character encoding system used primarily for representing Korean text on computers. It is an extension of the earlier EUC-KR encoding and is widely used in South Korea.

Code Page 932 (CP932) uses different byte sequences to represent different types of characters:

  • Single-Byte Characters
    The valid lead byte ranges for single-byte sequences are as follows:
    • 0x00-0x7F
  • Two-Byte Characters
    The valid lead byte ranges for double-byte sequences are as follows:
    • 0x81-0xFE

    The valid trail byte ranges for double-byte sequences are as follows:
    • 0x41-0xFE
